[2026-05-19T02:35:44.035Z] [TOOL_RESULT] 1	# Settings Screen Specification
2	
3	## 1. Screen Title
4	
5	**Title:** Settings
6	**Widget Name:** `SettingsScreen`
7	**Screen ID:** `settings`
8	
9	---
10	
11	## 2. Purpose
12	
13	The Settings screen allows users to manage their personal profile, configure notification preferences, export app data, and view legal/version information. It is a structured preference screen organized into four themed sections: Profile, Notifications, Data, and About.
14	
15	---
16	
17	## 3. Route
18	
19	**Route:** `/settings`
20	**Navigation Type:** Push (from Profile tab or Settings icon in Home AppBar)
21	**Swipe-back:** Enabled (dismisses to previous screen)
22	
23	---
24	
25	## 4. Design Tokens
26	
27	### Colors (Light Theme)
28	
29	| Token | Hex | Usage |
30	|---|---|---|
31	| `lavenderBloom` | `#7C3AED` | Primary actions, section headers, AppBar title |
32	| `lavenderTint` | `#F5F3FF` | Scaffold background |
33	| `morningMist` | `#FAFAFA` | Card backgrounds |
34	| `deepGraphite` | `#1F2937` | Primary text (titles, names) |
35	| `stoneGrey` | `#6B7280` | Secondary text, descriptions |
36	| `mistyBorder` | `#E5E7EB` | List item borders, toggles off state |
37	| `softCoral` | `#EF4444` | Clear data / destructive actions |
38	| `softMint` | `#6EE7B7` | Success states (export complete) |
39	| `warmWhite` | `#FFFFFF` | Card surfaces, bottom sheets |
40	
41	### Typography (Nunito)
42	
43	| Style | Size | Weight | Line Height | Usage |
44	|---|---|---|---|---|
45	| `titleLarge` | 20sp | 600 | 28sp | Screen title |
46	| `titleMedium` | 16sp | 600 | 24sp | Section headers |
47	| `bodyMedium` | 14sp | 400 | 20sp | List item titles, field labels |
48	| `bodySmall` | 14sp | 400 | 20sp | Descriptions, secondary text |
49	| `caption` | 12sp | 400 | 16sp | Metadata, hints, version text |
50	
51	### Spacing (8pt Base)
52	
53	| Token | Value |
54	|---|---|
55	| `xs` | 8dp |
56	| `md` | 16dp |
57	| `lg` | 24dp |
58	
59	### Corner Radius
60	
61	| Token | Value |
62	|---|---|
63	| `card` | 16dp |
64	| `listItem` | 12dp |
65	
66	### Motion
67	
68	| Motion | Duration | Curve |
69	|---|---|---|
70	| Screen push transition | 300ms | `Curves.easeInOut` |
71	| List item stagger reveal | 50ms delay between items | `Curves.easeOut` |
72	| Toggle switch thumb | 200ms | `Curves.easeOut` |
73	| Card tap feedback | 200ms | `Curves.easeOut` (scale to 98%) |
74	| Export success toast | 300ms fade in/out | `Curves.easeOut` |
75	
76	---
77	
78	## 5. Layout Rules
79	
80	### Scaffold Structure
81	
82	```
83	Scaffold
84	├── AppBar
85	│   ├── Title: "Settings" (titleLarge, deepGraphite)
86	│   ├── Back button (leading, 48dp touch target)
87	│   └── No trailing icons
88	├── BottomNavigationBar: Hidden
89	├── FAB: None
90	└── Body: ListView (sections separated by 24dp spacing)
91	```
92	
93	### AppBar Behavior
94	- Background: lavenderTint (#F5F3FF), transparent feel
95	- Title: centered or left-aligned, SemiBold 20sp, deepGraphite
96	- Back button: icon button with lavenderBloom color on tap
97	- No actions/trailing widgets
98	
99	### Body Layout
100	- Vertical `ListView` with `SliverAppBar` disabled (standard AppBar only)
101	- Cards are wrapped in `Padding` with 16dp horizontal margin
102	- 24dp vertical spacing between sections
103	- 12dp vertical spacing between items within a section
104	
105	### Bottom Navigation Bar
106	- Hidden on this screen (navType: push)
107	
108	---
109	
110	## 6. Sections
111	
112	### Section 1: Profile
113	
114	**Card:** `Card` with morningMist background, 16dp corner radius, 16dp internal padding.
115	
116	**Content:**
117	- **Name field** — `TextFormField` or tappable row that opens inline edit or bottom sheet. Label: "Name", value from `UserPreferences.name`.
118	- **Due date row** — Tappable list tile showing due date. Label: "Due Date", value from `PregnancyProfile.dueDate` (also stored in `UserPreferences.dueDate`). Tapping triggers `showDatePicker` bottom sheet.
119	
120	**Data Requirements:**
121	- `UserPreferencesProvider` — `name` field
122	- `PregnancyProfileProvider` — `dueDate` field
123	
124	**Interactive Elements:**
125	- Name tap → inline edit or bottom sheet with `TextEditingController`
126	- Due date tap → `showDatePicker` bottom sheet, saves to both providers
127	
128	---
129	
130	### Section 2: Notifications
131	
132	**Card:** `Card` with morningMist background, 16dp corner radius, 16dp internal padding.
133	
134	**Content:**
135	A `Column` of `SwitchListTile` widgets, one per notification category:
136	1. **Daily Reminders** — `UserPreferences.notifications.dailyReminders`
137	2. **Symptom Alerts** — `UserPreferences.notifications.symptomAlerts`
138	3. **Appointment Reminders** — `UserPreferences.notifications.appointmentReminders`
139	4. **Weekly Digest** — `UserPreferences.notifications.weeklyDigest`
140	
141	Each switch:
142	- Title: notification category name (titleMedium, deepGraphite)
143	- Subtitle: brief description (bodySmall, stoneGrey)
144	- Active track color: lavenderBloom; inactive track: mistyBorder
145	
146	**Data Requirements:**
147	- `UserPreferencesProvider` — `notificationsEnabled`, individual category flags
148	
149	**Interactive Elements:**
150	- Toggle switch → `UserPreferencesProvider.updateNotification(category, enabled)`
151	- 200ms thumb slide animation
152	
153	---
154	
155	### Section 3: Data
156	
157	**Card:** `Card` with morningMist background, 16dp corner radius, 16dp internal padding.
158	
159	**Content:**
160	Two action rows:
161	1. **Export Data** — `InkWell` or `ListTile` with icon and label. Tap → generates JSON/CSV file of all user data, triggers system share sheet.
162	2. **Clear All Data** — `ListTile` with icon and label in softCoral color. Tap → `AlertDialog` confirmation ("Are you sure? This action cannot be undone."), then calls `UserPreferencesProvider.clearAll()`.
163	
164	**Data Requirements:**
165	- `UserPreferencesProvider` — `clearAll()` method
166	- Export uses all provider data (pregnancy profile, mood entries, weight entries, health log)
167	
168	**Interactive Elements:**
169	- Export tap → generate file → `Share.share()` system share sheet
170	- Clear tap → `showDialog()` with `AlertDialog` → confirmation calls `clearAll()` and shows success snackbar
171	
172	---
173	
174	### Section 4: About
175	
176	**Card:** `Card` with morningMist background, 16dp corner radius, 16dp internal padding.
177	
178	**Content:**
179	Three rows:
180	1. **App Version** — Static text row: "Version" label + version string from `pubspec.yaml` (e.g., "1.0.0"). Non-interactive.
181	2. **Privacy Policy** — `ListTile` with icon and label. Tap → opens external URL (e.g., `https://example.com/privacy`).
182	3. **Terms of Service** — `ListTile` with icon and label. Tap → opens external URL (e.g., `https://example.com/terms`).
183	
184	**Interactive Elements:**
185	- Privacy Policy tap → `url_launcher.launchUrl()` with privacy policy URL
186	- Terms of Service tap → `url_launcher.launchUrl()` with terms URL
187	
188	---
189	
190	## 7. Data
191	
192	### Entities
193	
194	| Entity | Provider | Key Fields |
195	|---|---|---|
196	| `UserPreferences` | `UserPreferencesProvider` | `name`, `notificationsEnabled`, `dueDate` |
197	| `PregnancyProfile` | `PregnancyProfileProvider` | `dueDate`, `currentWeek` |
198	
199	### Provider Scope
200	
201	- `UserPreferencesProvider` — manages name, notification preferences, due date (shared with PregnancyProfile)
202	- `PregnancyProfileProvider` — manages due date, lastPeriodDate, currentWeek
203	
204	### Export File Format
205	
206	JSON format containing:
207	```json
208	{
209	  "exportDate": "ISO8601 timestamp",
210	  "user": { "name": "...", "dueDate": "..." },
211	  "pregnancyProfile": { ... },
212	  "moodEntries": [ ... ],
213	  "weightEntries": [ ... ],
214	  "symptomEntries": [ ... ],
215	  "cycleEntries": [ ... ]
216	}
217	```
218	
219	---
220	
221	## 8. Motion
222	
223	### Screen Transition
224	- **Duration:** 300ms
225	- **Curve:** `Curves.easeInOut`
226	- **Type:** Slide + fade (standard push transition)
227	
228	### List Item Reveal
229	- **Stagger:** 50ms between each item (from top to bottom)
230	- **Type:** Fade + slight slide up
231	- **Curve:** `Curves.easeOut`
232	
233	### Toggle Switch
234	- **Duration:** 200ms
235	- **Type:** Thumb slide, track color transition
236	
237	### Card Tap Feedback
238	- **Duration:** 200ms
239	- **Type:** Scale to 98%, then return to 100%
240	- **Curve:** `Curves.easeOut`
241	
242	### Export Success
243	- **Duration:** 300ms
244	- **Type:** SnackBar fade in from bottom, auto-dismiss after 3s
245	
246	---
247	
248	## 9. Accessibility
249	
250	### Semantic Labels
251	- **Name field:** "User name, [current name], double tap to edit"
252	- **Due date:** "Due date, [formatted date], double tap to change"
253	- **Notification toggles:** "[Category name], notifications [enabled/disabled], double tap to toggle"
254	- **Export Data:** "Export data, double tap to save and share your data"
255	- **Clear All Data:** "Clear all data, double tap to delete all app data. This action cannot be undone."
256	- **Privacy Policy:** "Privacy policy, opens in browser"
257	- **Terms of Service:** "Terms of service, opens in browser"
258	
259	### Touch Targets
260	- All interactive list items: minimum 56dp height
261	- All switches: 48dp minimum touch target
262	- All buttons: 48dp minimum height
263	
264	### Focus Order
265	1. Name field
266	2. Due date row
267	3. Daily Reminders toggle
268	4. Symptom Alerts toggle
269	5. Appointment Reminders toggle
270	6. Weekly Digest toggle
271	7. Export Data
272	8. Clear All Data
273	9. Privacy Policy
274	10. Terms of Service
275	
276	### Color Contrast
277	- Primary text (deepGraphite #1F2937) on morningMist (#FAFAFA): 12.8:1 ratio (AA compliant)
278	- Secondary text (stoneGrey #6B7280) on morningMist: 4.6:1 ratio (AA compliant)
279	- All text meets WCAG 2.1 AA contrast requirements
280	
281	---
282	
283	## 10. Anti-Patterns
284	
285	### Do NOT
286	- Use platform default colors — all colors from design token palette
287	- Show bottom navigation bar on this screen (hidden by navType: push)
288	- Use `AlertDialog` for anything other than destructive confirmation (clear data)
289	- Place critical actions (clear data) outside thumb zone (bottom two-thirds of screen)
290	- Use Inter or Roboto — Nunito only
291	- Use sharp corners — all cards 16dp radius, list items 12dp radius
292	- Use generic "OK" button labels — use action-specific labels ("Delete", "Cancel", "Export")
293	- Show FAB on this screen
294	- Use hardcoded strings — extract to localization keys
